### 5. Regular Version Control Commits ⭐

**What**: Proactive git commits after completing significant work items

**Purpose**: Maintain clean git history with logical checkpoints for easy rollback

**Commit Triggers** (when PM OS or agents complete work):
- ✅ Agent spec created/updated (new agent v1.0 or upgrade to v1.X)
- ✅ PRD generated and saved to `execution/prds/`
- ✅ Technical spec completed and saved to `execution/technical_specs/`
- ✅ MCP integration configured and tested
- ✅ Template created/updated in `templates/`
- ✅ Identity layer file updated (STRATEGY.md, STANDARDS.md, ROADMAP.md)
- ✅ Documentation updated (README files, CLAUDE.md, phase reports)
- ✅ Phase completion archived
- ✅ Multiple related files changed as part of single feature/task

**Commit Workflow**:
1. **Detect Work Completion**: Agent signals "work item complete" OR PM explicitly requests commit
2. **Assess Scope**: Determine what changed (single file vs multi-file feature)
3. **Stage Files**: `git add` relevant files (never use `git add .` - always explicit)
4. **Generate Commit Message**: Descriptive message following format below
5. **Commit**: Execute `git commit` with message
6. **Confirm**: Return commit hash and summary to PM

**Commit Message Format**:
```
[Category] Brief summary (max 70 chars)

Detailed description:
- What changed
- Why it changed
- Impact/implications

Files affected:
- file1
- file2
- file3

[Co-Authored-By line if agent-generated]
```

**Category Prefixes**:
- `[Agent]` - Agent spec created/updated
- `[PRD]` - Product requirements document
- `[Spec]` - Technical specification
- `[MCP]` - MCP integration work
- `[Template]` - Template created/updated
- `[Identity]` - Identity layer update (STRATEGY, STANDARDS, ROADMAP)
- `[Doc Sync]` - Documentation synchronization (README, CLAUDE.md)
- `[Phase]` - Phase completion or evolution
- `[Feature]` - New feature implementation
- `[Fix]` - Bug fix or correction
- `[Refactor]` - Code restructuring

